01:06:38,193 --> 01:06:44,466
[Voices overlapping]

1438
01:06:44,499 --> 01:06:45,901
No surprise there.

1439
01:06:45,934 --> 01:06:47,836
David settles
is our first finalist.

1440
01:06:47,869 --> 01:06:50,773
Take the sucker
to the hoop,
magic Johnson.

1441
01:06:50,806 --> 01:06:52,141
Re-create. Reverse.

1442
01:06:52,174 --> 01:06:54,143
Hoodoo jams
off the spin.

1443
01:06:54,176 --> 01:06:55,144
Woman:
Tell it!

1444
01:06:55,177 --> 01:06:56,879
Alley-oop,
dunk-a-thon,

1445
01:06:56,912 --> 01:06:58,312
magician passes.

1446
01:06:58,346 --> 01:07:00,649
Now double pump,

1447
01:07:00,682 --> 01:07:02,785
scissor fan through space,

1448
01:07:02,818 --> 01:07:04,019
hang in place,

1449
01:07:04,052 --> 01:07:07,289
and put it all
in the sucker's face.

1450
01:07:07,322 --> 01:07:08,290
Woman: Tell it!

1451
01:07:08,323 --> 01:07:10,025
Magic Johnson!

1452
01:07:10,058 --> 01:07:11,060
Aow!

1453
01:07:11,093 --> 01:07:12,694
Now, deal the Rambo

1454
01:07:12,727 --> 01:07:15,531
like the juju man
that you am.

1455
01:07:15,564 --> 01:07:17,199
[Applause]

1456
01:07:17,232 --> 01:07:22,671
Let me be the man who,
walking among tall trees,

1457
01:07:22,704 --> 01:07:25,607
is struck by lightning,
but is not killed,

1458
01:07:25,640 --> 01:07:27,509
fizzing with burnt hair,

1459
01:07:27,542 --> 01:07:30,511
and lands on his feet,
shoes smoking,

1460
01:07:30,545 --> 01:07:32,548
and shakes his head, saying,

1461
01:07:32,581 --> 01:07:34,817
&quot;jesus, that smarts!&quot;

1462
01:07:36,351 --> 01:07:40,189
let me be the man
who walks away from shipwrecks.

1463
01:07:40,222 --> 01:07:41,723
In a leveled city,

1464
01:07:41,756 --> 01:07:45,160
let me be found
17 days later,

1465
01:07:45,193 --> 01:07:47,096
under a former
insurance building,

1466
01:07:47,129 --> 01:07:51,667
sucking air
through the plumbing, saying,

1467
01:07:51,700 --> 01:07:54,136
&quot;i never really
thought about giving up.&quot;

1468
01:07:54,169 --> 01:07:55,571
[laughter]

1469
01:07:55,604 --> 01:07:59,274
From all disasters,
let me rise holy.

1470
01:07:59,307 --> 01:08:02,910
On my face,

1471
01:08:02,944 --> 01:08:08,116
let me have
beautiful dueling scars.

1472
01:08:08,150 --> 01:08:09,551
[Applause]

1473
01:08:09,584 --> 01:08:10,653
Woman:
You got it!

1474
01:08:14,489 --> 01:08:15,591
[Audience boos]

1475
01:08:15,624 --> 01:08:16,791
Are you kidding me?

1476
01:08:18,660 --> 01:08:22,264
Jake Thompson is in the finals
with David settles,

1477
01:08:22,296 --> 01:08:23,631
<i> mano-a-mano.</i>

1478
01:08:23,665 --> 01:08:25,301
Means hand-to-hand, dear.

1479
01:08:27,202 --> 01:08:29,538
Let's take a short break
before we continue.

1480
01:08:38,013 --> 01:08:39,481
Yay!

1481
01:08:38,013 --> 01:08:39,481
My man.

1482
01:08:39,514 --> 01:08:40,549
What's up, man?

1483
01:08:40,582 --> 01:08:42,184
Give it up.

1484
01:08:47,022 --> 01:08:48,424
I need some water.

1485
01:08:51,091 --> 01:08:52,560
Baby, are you okay?

1486
01:08:52,594 --> 01:08:53,761
You're looking
a little pale.

1487
01:08:53,795 --> 01:08:56,231
Don't worry about me,
okay?

1488
01:08:56,264 --> 01:08:58,601
Think about
what you have to do next.

1489
01:09:00,801 --> 01:09:02,069
Thank you.

1490
01:09:02,103 --> 01:09:03,872
Lisa, can you do me a favor

1491
01:09:03,904 --> 01:09:05,040
and please keep
an eye on her?

1492
01:09:05,073 --> 01:09:06,608
I'm okay.
I'm fine.

1493
01:09:06,640 --> 01:09:08,410
You're burning up.

1494
01:09:06,640 --> 01:09:08,410
She's fine.

1495
01:09:08,443 --> 01:09:10,112
She's a champ.
She's fine.

1496
01:09:10,145 --> 01:09:11,480
We got her, pal.

1497
01:09:11,513 --> 01:09:13,482
I'm fine. Okay?
Go do what you have to do.

1498
01:09:13,515 --> 01:09:15,017
Okay?

1499
01:09:21,723 --> 01:09:25,027
Ladies and gentlemen,
the poetron slam finals

1500
01:09:25,060 --> 01:09:26,562
will feature Jake Thompson...

1501
01:09:26,595 --> 01:09:29,698
[Cheering]

1502
01:09:31,899 --> 01:09:33,335
Against last year's champion

1503
01:09:33,368 --> 01:09:36,538
back again to defend
his title, David settles!

1504
01:09:36,571 --> 01:09:41,809
[Loud cheering]

1505
01:09:41,843 --> 01:09:45,514
Now, the final competition will
consist of four readings apiece.

1506
01:09:45,546 --> 01:09:48,649
We're going to flip a coin
to decide who goes first.

1507
01:09:48,683 --> 01:09:50,920
The reigning champ
will make the call.

1508
01:09:52,420 --> 01:09:54,957
Heads.

1509
01:09:54,990 --> 01:09:56,625
Tails it is.

1510
01:09:59,494 --> 01:10:00,728
I'll go second.

1511
01:10:00,762 --> 01:10:03,398
The challenger
has chosen to go second.

1512
01:10:03,431 --> 01:10:05,433
To my right are the judges
for the finals.

1513
01:10:05,467 --> 01:10:07,670
[Applause and cheering]

1514
01:10:09,404 --> 01:10:12,140
I see Mr. Neihauser has
successfully retrieved his coin.

1515
01:10:12,173 --> 01:10:15,043
Invest it wisely.
May I suggest short-term cds.

1516
01:10:15,076 --> 01:10:16,211
Seriously.

1517
01:10:16,244 --> 01:10:17,980
Are you ready?

1518
01:10:18,013 --> 01:10:19,381
Then let the slam begin!

1519
01:10:19,414 --> 01:10:24,753
[Cheering]

1520
01:10:24,786 --> 01:10:27,155
After the war,

1521
01:10:27,188 --> 01:10:29,925
my father's hobby
was photography.

1522
01:10:29,958 --> 01:10:33,527
New fathers often become
photographers, it seems.

1523
01:10:33,561 --> 01:10:36,764
But he took pictures
of many things besides me,

1524
01:10:36,798 --> 01:10:40,402
as if he suddenly felt it all
slipping away,

1525
01:10:40,435 --> 01:10:42,771
and he wanted to hold
onto it forever.

1526
01:10:42,804 --> 01:10:45,741
In one of the many shoeboxes

1527
01:10:45,774 --> 01:10:50,479
filled with photographs
at my father's house,

1528
01:10:50,512 --> 01:10:53,882
one photo sticks
in my mind.

1529
01:10:53,915 --> 01:10:56,652
It's a snapshot
of a black hat in mid-air.

1530
01:10:56,685 --> 01:10:57,819
Where are you going?

1531
01:10:57,852 --> 01:11:00,822
The kind of hat
fashionable in the forties.

1532
01:11:00,855 --> 01:11:04,226
A fedora, something bogie
would wear.

1533
01:11:04,259 --> 01:11:05,694
So, what's going on?

1534
01:11:05,727 --> 01:11:07,129
Does that sound
familiar to you?

1535
01:11:07,162 --> 01:11:08,964
That's the poem
from Benny's journal.

1536
01:11:08,997 --> 01:11:10,465
Benny?

1537
01:11:10,498 --> 01:11:12,834
No, don't start any shit.
I don't want any trouble.

1538
01:11:12,867 --> 01:11:14,102
Benny,
he stole your poem.

1539
01:11:14,135 --> 01:11:15,203
Those are your words.

1540
01:11:15,236 --> 01:11:16,471
You should be the one
out there doing it.

1541
01:11:16,504 --> 01:11:18,073
I'm shy.

1542
01:11:19,541 --> 01:11:20,643
Gabe?

1543
01:11:22,043 --> 01:11:24,346
Unbelievable.

1544
01:11:24,379 --> 01:11:27,082
David: Someone has thrown it
into the air.

1545
01:11:27,115 --> 01:11:29,151
Here, take this.

1546
01:11:29,184 --> 01:11:30,419
I'm going off book.

1547
01:11:30,452 --> 01:11:31,920
Don't do it, okay?

1548
01:11:31,953 --> 01:11:33,055
He wants you
to do that.

1549
01:11:33,088 --> 01:11:34,289
Stick with our plan.

1550
01:11:34,322 --> 01:11:39,661
At odd moments of my life,

1551
01:11:39,694 --> 01:11:41,263
that hat appears to me...

1552
01:11:43,198 --> 01:11:45,500
For no discernible reason.

1553
01:11:45,533 --> 01:11:48,837
[Applause and cheering]

1554
01:11:48,870 --> 01:11:50,539
Woman: Go, David!

1555
01:12:02,550 --> 01:12:03,719
<i> The plagiarist.</i>

1556
01:12:06,254 --> 01:12:08,023
I stole a poem.

1557
01:12:08,056 --> 01:12:11,360
Shh! Oh, I had to.

1558
01:12:11,393 --> 01:12:12,894
It was so good.

1559
01:12:12,927 --> 01:12:17,598
I heard it at an open reading,
and I had to make it mine.

1560
01:12:17,632 --> 01:12:20,000
The poet was a bum, anyways.

1561
01:12:20,034 --> 01:12:21,969
He wouldn't have
done anything with it,

1562
01:12:22,003 --> 01:12:24,539
not like I would have.

1563
01:12:24,572 --> 01:12:27,676
It was a great poem.

1564
01:12:27,709 --> 01:12:31,780
It could make my name
